<task id="004" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D1-04 Extend `ChatSession` model with `UploadedFiles[]` manifest</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>2 hours</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 1 — Platform Extensions</phase>
    <wave>P1-G3 (parallel-safe with 005; no dependencies; blocks 007 cleanup job)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <tags>bff, model, session</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the existing `ChatSession` record at
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs` with a new
    `UploadedFiles` property of type `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;` and introduce the
    `ChatSessionFile` record alongside it. `ChatSessionFile` carries the per-file manifest
    used by (a) the session-scoped RAG retrieval path (extended in task 002), (b) the
    session-files cleanup `IHostedService` (task 007), and (c) the chat-pane file-chip UX
    (Phase 2, task 020). The manifest property MUST round-trip cleanly through the existing
    triple-tier persistence: Redis hot tier (24h sliding TTL, `IDistributedCache`), Cosmos
    DB warm tier (`ISessionPersistenceService` write-through), and Dataverse cold-tier
    audit (`IChatDataverseRepository`).

    Per spec §4.4 + NFR-02 + project CLAUDE.md §3.8: the per-session manifest is hard-capped
    at 20 files (rejects 21st upload). Files smaller than 500 tokens skip chunking
    (single-chunk index; downstream contract consumed by tasks 003 + 006 + 007). Aggressive
    cleanup-on-session-end (cleanup job task 007 owns this). Backward compatibility is
    binding — existing `ChatSession` consumers and persistence paths MUST keep working
    unchanged when `UploadedFiles` is null / empty / absent on the wire.

    This is the model-only deliverable D1-04. Downstream consumers (task 007 cleanup job,
    task 020 chat-pane file chips, task 003 indexing pipeline) depend on the SHAPE this
    task ships. Get the shape right; resist scope creep into orchestration.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 developer with deep familiarity with the Spaarke BFF AI chat session
    storage model (Redis hot + Cosmos warm write-through + Dataverse cold per ADR-009 +
    D-06). Comfortable extending C# `record` types additively and verifying JSON
    serialization round-trips across three persistence tiers without breaking existing
    consumers.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The `ChatSession` record at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs`
    is extended with an additional optional `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;? UploadedFiles`
    property (default `null` for backward compatibility); a new `ChatSessionFile` record
    is introduced in the same namespace with the six fields specified in design.md §4.4
    (`FileId`, `FileName`, `ContentType`, `SizeBytes`, `SearchDocumentIdsCsv`,
    `UploadedAt`). The 20-file per-session cap is encoded as a const on `ChatSession`
    (`MaxUploadedFiles = 20`) and the &lt;500-token chunking-skip threshold is documented in
    XML doc-comments on the relevant property/field for downstream consumers. A
    serialization round-trip test confirms the manifest survives Redis JSON serialization,
    Cosmos write-through, and Dataverse cold-tier audit unchanged. BFF builds clean,
    publish-size delta is within budget (≤ +0.5 MB target, ≤ +1 MB ceiling per project
    CLAUDE.md §3.6), and existing `ChatSession` consumers compile + behave unchanged.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-design">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-index">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
    <file purpose="target-model">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs</file>
    <file purpose="session-manager">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs</file>
    <file purpose="session-persistence">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/ISessionPersistenceService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="dataverse-repo">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Dataverse/IChatDataverseRepository.cs</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="module-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="chat-architecture">docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (reuse mandate)">MUST extend the existing `ChatSession` record at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs` — do NOT introduce a parallel session model or a new session-management layer (per spec §2.11 explicitly prohibits parallel session management to `ChatSessionManager`). `ChatSessionFile` is a NEW record type but lives in the existing `Sprk.Bff.Api.Models.Ai.Chat` namespace as part of the same model surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (no new feature flags)">MUST NOT introduce a new feature flag for the manifest property. `UploadedFiles` is unconditionally part of the model. Population is gated by callers (uploads), not by configuration.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.8 + spec NFR-02">Hard cap = 20 files per session (rejects 21st upload). Encode as `public const int MaxUploadedFiles = 20;` on `ChatSession` so callers can reference one source of truth. Files &lt; 500 tokens skip chunking (single-chunk index) — document in XML doc-comments on `ChatSessionFile` so downstream consumers (task 003 indexing pipeline, task 007 cleanup) read the contract from the model.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-009 (storage seam)">Manifest persistence is INHERITED from existing triple-tier storage: Redis hot tier (24h sliding TTL via `IDistributedCache`), Cosmos warm tier (`ISessionPersistenceService` write-through per D-06), Dataverse cold-tier audit (`IChatDataverseRepository`). This task MUST NOT modify `ChatSessionManager`'s storage flow; the manifest is an additive `ChatSession` property that rides existing serialization.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010 (DI minimalism)">N/A for this task — no new service registrations. Confirm in task notes that zero new `services.AddXxx()` lines were added.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014 (tenant isolation)">`ChatSessionFile` records belong to a single `ChatSession` which carries `TenantId`. Manifest entries inherit tenant scoping from the parent session. Do NOT add a redundant `TenantId` on `ChatSessionFile`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019 (ProblemDetails)">N/A for this task (no endpoint surface). Endpoints that consume the manifest (e.g., task 014 summarize endpoint) own ProblemDetails error mapping for "21st-file-rejection".</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 (Auth v2)">N/A for this task (no auth-bearing surface). Confirm no token snapshots are added.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 + R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 (BFF publish-size)">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/` after the change. Measure compressed output. Report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline (~45.65 MB) in task notes. Hard ceiling 60 MB; R5 target delta ≤ +0.5 MB, max +1 MB. A model-only change should produce a delta &lt; 0.1 MB; anything larger triggers investigation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7 (test obligation per task)">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests. This task modifies `Models/` (not `Services/`), but the model is consumed by `ChatSessionManager`; therefore add at minimum a serialization round-trip test under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Models/Ai/Chat/`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (backward compatibility)">`UploadedFiles` MUST be nullable (`IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;? = null` default) so existing `ChatSession` constructions, deserialized payloads from already-running production sessions, and pre-R5 Cosmos / Dataverse records continue to work. A null / absent manifest is semantically equivalent to "no files uploaded".</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (additive property only)">MUST be the LAST positional record parameter (or use a non-positional property initializer) so existing positional `new ChatSession(...)` calls don't break. Add the property AFTER `AdditionalDocumentIds` (current last parameter).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff/chat-session-model + persistence-tiers</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-009-caching-storage-seams.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching-tenant-isolation.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="ChatSessionFile shape (binding)" location="projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md §4.4">
        The `ChatSessionFile` record shape is specified verbatim in design.md §4.4:
        ```csharp
        record ChatSessionFile(
          string FileId,                 // stable session-scoped ID
          string FileName,
          string ContentType,
          long SizeBytes,
          string SearchDocumentIdsCsv,   // IDs in spaarke-session-files index (CSV)
          DateTimeOffset UploadedAt);
        ```
        Implement exactly this shape — no additional fields beyond these six. The CSV
        format for `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` is intentional (compact, Redis-friendly, no
        nested arrays in the hot-tier blob).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Additive record extension (positional record)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs">
        `ChatSession` is a positional `record`. Append `UploadedFiles` AFTER
        `AdditionalDocumentIds` (the current last parameter) with a default of `null` to
        preserve existing call sites. Add XML doc-comments matching the style of existing
        parameters. Add the `MaxUploadedFiles = 20` const inside the record body.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Triple-tier serialization round-trip" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs">
        `ChatSessionManager` uses `System.Text.Json` (`JsonSerializer`) for Redis-cache
        serialization and forwards the same `ChatSession` object to `ISessionPersistenceService`
        (Cosmos write-through) + `IChatDataverseRepository` (cold-tier audit). Because the
        manifest property rides the existing serialization paths, NO change to
        `ChatSessionManager` is required — the round-trip test must PROVE this empirically
        rather than rely on it.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5's "Summarize a Document" vertical slice depends on the chat agent knowing which
      files the user has uploaded into the current session, where each file's chunks live
      in the new `spaarke-session-files` AI Search index (task 001), and when each file
      was uploaded so cleanup logic (task 007) can identify abandoned-session leftovers.
      The existing `ChatSession` record carries `AdditionalDocumentIds` (a flat string
      list of SPE document IDs pinned to the session) but lacks the richer per-file
      manifest required. D1-04 is the model extension that backs all four R5 surfaces
      consuming session-file state: (1) RAG retrieval (task 002 `sessionId` filter route);
      (2) indexing writes (task 003 pipeline parameterization); (3) cleanup job (task 007);
      (4) chat-pane file-chip UX (task 020).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">
        Task 001 provisions the `spaarke-session-files` AI Search index. This task (004)
        does NOT depend on 001 directly — model + index are independent concerns — but
        the `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` field on `ChatSessionFile` only has meaning once the
        index exists. They can land in any order; 001 is technically the downstream
        consumer of this model when indexing pipeline writes (task 003) populate the field.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 005 (D1-05) — adds `FieldDelta` variant to `AnalysisChunk`. Sibling
        wave-mate (P1-G3); both are model-only edits in different files; parallel-safe.</item>
      <item>Task 007 (D1-07) — Session-files cleanup `IHostedService`. Direct downstream
        consumer of `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` — sweeps `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` entries
        for sessions not in active Redis set.</item>
      <item>Task 020 (D2-11) — Chat-pane file chips. Frontend consumer of the manifest
        via the chat session API; per-file remove must dispatch both manifest removal AND
        index document removal (the latter via task 007's cleanup path).</item>
      <item>Task 003 (D1-03) — Indexing pipeline parameterization. Writes session-files
        index documents and is the natural producer of `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` values.</item>
      <item>R3 added `AdditionalDocumentIds` (last positional parameter on `ChatSession`).
        That property is structurally adjacent but semantically distinct — it pins
        pre-existing SPE documents for cross-reference; `UploadedFiles` carries the
        manifest for files the user actively uploaded into the chat session. Both
        properties coexist.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL Declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, run `context-handoff` and request `/compact`. Output
      mandatory rigor-level declaration per CLAUDE.md §8:
      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: BFF model code change (.cs); downstream consumers in 4 R5 tasks
         (007 cleanup, 003 indexing, 020 chat-pane, 014 summarize endpoint); persistence
         contract spans 3 storage tiers; backward compatibility is binding.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 1–10 below with code-review + adr-check at 9.5.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm task 004 status is 🔲, parallel-safe = ✅,
      dependencies = none. Read `current-task.md` to verify no prior R5 task is mid-flight
      on the same files. Read project `CLAUDE.md` §3.1 (reuse mandate), §3.2 (no new
      flags), §3.6 (BFF publish-size), §3.7 (test obligation), §3.8 (20-file cap).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically:
      (a) Read `ChatSession.cs` in full and identify the current record-parameter order;
      (b) Read `ChatSessionManager.cs` to confirm `JsonSerializer` is the Redis
      serialization mechanism and that `ChatSession` flows unmodified to
      `ISessionPersistenceService` (Cosmos) + `IChatDataverseRepository` (cold);
      (c) Read design.md §4.4 (the binding shape spec for `ChatSessionFile`);
      (d) Read spec NFR-02 (20-file cap + 500-token threshold + aggressive cleanup).
      Confirm the design.md §4.4 shape is unchanged since plan v1.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Plan Implementation">
      Sketch the diff before editing:
      (a) Append `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;? UploadedFiles = null` to `ChatSession`
          (after `AdditionalDocumentIds`);
      (b) Add `public const int MaxUploadedFiles = 20;` inside the record body;
      (c) Author XML doc-comments for the new property + the new record;
      (d) Create new file or in-file declaration of `ChatSessionFile` (decision: same
          file `ChatSession.cs` for tight cohesion, or sibling `ChatSessionFile.cs` for
          separation-of-concerns — pick same-file given the record is tightly bound to
          its parent and the file is small);
      (e) Plan the round-trip unit test at
          `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionSerializationTests.cs`
          (or extend existing test file if present).
      Confirm zero changes to `ChatSessionManager.cs`, `ISessionPersistenceService.cs`,
      or `IChatDataverseRepository.cs` — additive model property only.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Model Changes">
      Edit `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs`:
      (a) Add `ChatSessionFile` record with the six fields from design.md §4.4 + XML
          doc-comments. Document the &lt;500-token chunking-skip threshold + the
          `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` CSV-format contract in the XML docs;
      (b) Append `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;? UploadedFiles = null` to the
          `ChatSession` positional record (after `AdditionalDocumentIds`);
      (c) Add `public const int MaxUploadedFiles = 20;` inside the record body;
      (d) Add XML doc-comments referencing spec NFR-02 + project CLAUDE.md §3.8 +
          design.md §4.4.
      Build the BFF: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — MUST succeed clean
      with no new warnings.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify Backward Compatibility">
      Run `dotnet build` on the entire repo (`dotnet build`) to confirm no existing
      `ChatSession` consumers break. Run `dotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ChatSession`
      to confirm existing ChatSession-related tests still pass. If any test fails because
      of the new property, the property was not added additively-enough — fix before
      proceeding.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Author Round-Trip Serialization Test">
      Add a unit test at
      `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionSerializationTests.cs`
      (extending if a file exists) with at least these cases:
      (a) `ChatSession` with `UploadedFiles = null` serializes + deserializes via
          `System.Text.Json` round-trip identically (pre-R5 wire-compat);
      (b) `ChatSession` with empty `UploadedFiles = []` round-trips identically;
      (c) `ChatSession` with 20 `ChatSessionFile` entries round-trips with all 6 fields
          preserved including a `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` containing &gt; 1 comma-separated ID;
      (d) `MaxUploadedFiles` const is exposed as `20` (regression guard against drift
          from spec NFR-02).
      Run the test: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` — MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Triple-Tier Persistence (Empirical Round-Trip)">
      Because `ChatSession` flows unmodified through Redis (`JsonSerializer`) + Cosmos
      (`ISessionPersistenceService.UpsertAsync` accepts the same `ChatSession`) +
      Dataverse (`IChatDataverseRepository`), the unit-test JSON round-trip in Step 6
      proves Redis + Cosmos compatibility (both use `System.Text.Json` semantics).
      For Dataverse cold-tier audit: inspect `IChatDataverseRepository` to confirm whether
      it serializes the full `ChatSession` (in which case the JSON round-trip already
      covers it) OR cherry-picks specific fields (in which case verify `UploadedFiles` is
      NOT cherry-picked, meaning the cold tier intentionally does NOT carry the manifest
      — which matches NFR-02 "aggressive cleanup-on-session-end" + the cold-tier audit
      role). Document the finding in task notes; either outcome is acceptable as long as
      backward compatibility holds.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="BFF Publish-Size Verification (NFR-07 + CLAUDE.md §3.6)">
      Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
      Measure compressed output (zip the publish folder or use the existing
      publish-size measurement helper if one is available in `scripts/`). Compare to the
      ~45.65 MB baseline. Record absolute size + delta in task notes. Expected delta
      for a model-only change: &lt; 0.1 MB. If delta &gt; 0.5 MB, investigate before
      marking complete. If delta &gt; 1 MB, STOP and escalate per CLAUDE.md §3.6.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below. Confirm each is testable +
      passing. Record evidence per criterion in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against `ChatSession.cs` (and the new test file). Run
      `adr-check` skill against the same files; specifically verify:
      - ADR-009 (storage seam) — manifest persistence inherited via existing tiers; no
        new storage seam introduced
      - ADR-010 (DI minimalism) — zero new DI registrations
      - ADR-014 (tenant isolation) — manifest entries do NOT add a redundant `TenantId`
      - ADR-018 (Feature Flag Scope Discipline) — no new feature flag introduced
      - ADR-029 (BFF publish hygiene) — size delta within budget
      Both `code-review` and `adr-check` MUST pass before marking the task complete.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 004 🔲 → ✅.
      Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task per CLAUDE.md §7. Record in task
      notes (`notes/task-004-model-extension-evidence.md`):
      (a) The applied diff of `ChatSession.cs` (or a summary of additions);
      (b) The serialization-test results;
      (c) The Dataverse cold-tier audit finding from Step 7;
      (d) The BFF publish-size measurement + delta vs baseline (per CLAUDE.md §3.6);
      (e) Zero new DI registrations confirmed (ADR-010);
      (f) Zero new feature flags confirmed (CLAUDE.md §3.2).
      Report task completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + test the BFF; measure publish-size delta.</tool>
