  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`ChatSession.cs` exposes a new `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt;? UploadedFiles` property (default `null`) appended AFTER `AdditionalDocumentIds` in the positional record signature.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ChatSessionFile` record exists in namespace `Sprk.Bff.Api.Models.Ai.Chat` with exactly six fields matching design.md §4.4 verbatim: `FileId` (string), `FileName` (string), `ContentType` (string), `SizeBytes` (long), `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` (string), `UploadedAt` (DateTimeOffset).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`public const int MaxUploadedFiles = 20;` is declared on `ChatSession` and matches spec NFR-02 / R5 CLAUDE.md §3.8.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">XML doc-comments on `ChatSessionFile` document (a) the &lt;500-token chunking-skip threshold (per NFR-02) and (b) the `SearchDocumentIdsCsv` CSV-format contract.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` succeeds clean on the full repo with no new warnings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pre-existing `ChatSession`-related tests continue to pass without modification (backward compatibility verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Round-trip serialization test passes for: (a) `UploadedFiles = null`, (b) empty list, (c) 20-entry list with all six fields preserved (including multi-ID CSV) — proving Redis + Cosmos `System.Text.Json` compatibility.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dataverse cold-tier audit path is verified to either (a) carry the full `ChatSession` (manifest survives) or (b) intentionally cherry-pick fields excluding `UploadedFiles` (consistent with NFR-02 aggressive cleanup-on-session-end); finding recorded in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero new `services.AddXxx()` lines added anywhere (ADR-010); zero new feature flags (CLAUDE.md §3.2). Confirmed in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta measured and reported in task notes; delta &lt; +0.5 MB (target) and &lt; +1 MB (ceiling per CLAUDE.md §3.6); absolute size remains well under 60 MB hard ceiling.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
